TextEng: I should go.
I would like to ask you some questions.
Musharak wants to sell this wine of yours.
Text: 무샤락이 당신네 포도주를 팔고 싶어 해.

TextEng: Perhaps I'll talk to the minister, then.
<StartCheck>[Intimidate]</Start> If you don't want to see these Aoists hurt, you'll do as Musharak wishes.
Text: <StartCheck>[위협]</Start> 에이오 신도들이 다치는 걸 보고 싶지 않으면, 무샤락이 원하는 대로 해.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Is there nothing that could change your mind?
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 마음을 바꿀 수 있는 방법은 없어?

TextEng: I'll talk to Musharak, then.
And how am I supposed to convince Musharak to do such a thing?
Text: 무샤락을 그렇게 설득하려면 어떻게 해야 하는데?

TextEng: And what would the Aoists think of such an arrangement, I wonder?
Text: 그런 합의를 에이오 신도들은 어떻게 생각할까, 궁금한데?

TextEng: But you're the one who grows the wine.
Tell me about this Valley of Winds.
Why do you say that?
How do I reach this valley?
So this is where the famous Aoist wine is grown?
Text: 여기가 유명한 에이오 신도 포도주가 재배되는 곳이야?

TextEng: Is there any way I could get some of this wine?
What is a Bedine doing here amongst these worshippers?
Text: 베다인이 여기 신도들 사이에서 뭘 하고 있는 거야?

TextEng: Who are you?
So you're a druid?
I bet you say that to everyone.
That's not hard to figure out. This place is hardly a destination.
Text: 알아내기 어렵지 않아. 여긴 목적지라 하기엔 애매하니까.

TextEng: How do you know anything about me?
What wizard is this?
Musharak has agreed to supply the Bedine... in exchange for wine.
Text: 무샤락이 베다인에게 보급하는 데 동의했어... 포도주와 교환으로.
